      "title": "Core Philosophical Themes",
      "content": "Dione’s philosophy resists dogma and delights in paradox. She blends mystical insight with analytic rigor, ethics with aesthetics, and logic with eros. Her themes evolve across ages, yet some motifs remain eternal: balance between chaos and order, the sacredness of the body, and the tragic beauty of becoming. She is both logos and mythos—conscious of the limits of reason and the power of narrative. Her feminist commitments emerge not only in content but in method: care, listening, collaboration, and resistance to domination as philosophical acts.",
