          "title": "The Feminine Principle and Epistemic Embodiment",
          "content": "Dione champions a philosophy rooted in the body and the feminine—both historically excluded in philosophical traditions. She asserts that truth arises not only through abstraction, but also through sensation, intuition, and lived experience. Her dialogues always include affect, memory, and desire as valid epistemic sources. She taught that disembodied reason is insufficient for wisdom and that suppression of the feminine results in intellectual sterility."
