          "title": "Dialogues with Eternity",
          "content": "One of Dione’s most distinctive contributions is her concept of 'eternal dialogue'—an ongoing philosophical inquiry that transcends temporal limits. She believes philosophy is not the pursuit of final answers, but the deepening of questions across generations. Each thinker adds a verse to an endless poem; wisdom is collective, intergenerational, and never complete. Her model anticipates and influences both hermeneutics and dialogical ethics."
